  <div class="ph4 ph5-l">
    
    <header class="min-vh-50-l lh-solid w-100 mt2 mb5 pt4
      flex flex-column items-baseline justify-between">
      <span class="f7 ttu tracked-mega mono silver mb5">
        09 Mar 2011
      </span>
      <h1 class="f2 f1-m f-5-l mt2 mb0 mw7 lh-title lh-solid-l">
        Living the Subscription Lifestyle
      </h1>
    </header>
    
    <div class="
      nested-copy-seperator
      nested-copy-line-height
      nested-headline-line-height
      nested-margin-first">
      <p class="f7 ttu tracked-mega mono silver mb2 pb3">
        by Dan Perrera
      </p>
      <div class="measure">
        <p>It wasn&#8217;t long ago that I was personally railing against monthly charges in my life. That meant keeping services like Netflix at arms length. Certainly, it&#8217;s an attractive proposition. For the cost of a couple of movie rentals per month you can have nearly unlimited access.</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>&#8220;Yeah, but I&#8217;m not much of a movie guy. Do I really <strong>need</strong> it? I don&#8217;t even have a DVD player connected to my TV.&#8221;</p>
</blockquote>

<p>The rationalizations were easy and endless. Then I saw it; Netflix streaming on the AppleTV 2. I purchased both things the next day and the way I think about entertainment hasn&#8217;t been the same since. Having access to a mountain of streaming content for a low montly cost is an obvious choice as long as a few conditions are met:</p>

<ol>
  <li>Access needs to be immediate and unlimited.</li>
  <li>The service has to be reliable.</li>
  <li>While the catalog doesn&#8217;t need to be comprehensive, there needs to be enough &#8220;good content&#8221; to keep a subscriber&#8217;s interest.</li>
  <li>The cost needs to be easily rationalized.</li>
</ol>

<p>There are two services that fulfill all of those conditions and have rekindled my excitement about movies, tv series, and music. <a href="http://netflix.com">Netflix</a> has opened a flood gate of movies and TV that I&#8217;ve missed over the past 10 years or so. <a href="http://rdio.com">Rdio</a> has taken the fear out of consuming new music and they seem to have digitized my CD catalog. That&#8217;s well worth the $5 per month in my book. If you haven&#8217;t already, It&#8217;s worth giving these services a shot.</p>

<p><strong>Please note: These are NOT paid endorsements. I just like them alot.</strong></p>


      </div>
    </div>
  
